  <note line="69" original="pariccajā (syā. kaṃ.)" reference-line="30" id="7">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">pariccajanā</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="syā." source="thai">pariccajā</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="kaṃ." source="kaṃ.">pariccajā</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet>Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, saṅgho bhinno hoti. Saṅghe kho pana, bhikkhave, bhinne aññamaññaṃ akkosā ca honti, aññamaññaṃ paribhāsā ca honti, aññamaññaṃ parikkhepā ca honti, aññamaññaṃ pariccajanā </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="79" original="acchinnamūlako (ka.) a. ni. 4.160" reference-line="33" id="8">
    <extra> a. ni. 4.160</extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">chinnamūlako</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="ka." source="cambodian">acchinnamūlako</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet>Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū bahussutā āgatāgamā dhammadharā vinayadharā mātikādharā, te sakkaccaṃ suttantaṃ paraṃ vācenti; tesaṃ accayena na chinnamūlako </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="88" original="puggalaṃ puggalaṃ (sī. pī.)" reference-line="37" id="9">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">puggale puggalaṃ</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="sī." source="sri lanka">puggalaṃ puggalaṃ</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="pī." source="pali text society">puggalaṃ puggalaṃ</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet>, bhikkhave, puggalānaṃ kathā dukkathā puggale puggalaṃ </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="98" original="macchariyassa (sī. pī. ka.)" reference-line="37" id="10">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">maccharissa</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="sī." source="sri lanka">macchariyassa</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="pī." source="pali text society">macchariyassa</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="ka." source="cambodian">macchariyassa</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet> upanidhāya. Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ? Assaddhassa, bhikkhave, saddhākathā dukkathā; dussīlassa sīlakathā dukkathā; appassutassa bāhusaccakathā dukkathā; maccharissa </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="109" original="na sampassati (sī.)" reference-line="38" id="11">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">na samanupassati</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="sī." source="sri lanka">na sampassati</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet>Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, assaddhassa saddhākathā dukkathā? Assaddho, bhikkhave, saddhākathāya kacchamānāya abhisajjati kuppati byāpajjati patitthīyati kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti. Taṃ kissa hetu? Tañhi so, bhikkhave, saddhāsampadaṃ attani na samanupassati </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="118" original="okkamanto (ka.)" reference-line="50" id="12">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">okkanto</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="ka." source="cambodian">okkamanto</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet> Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu sārajjaṃ okkanto </snippet>
  </note>
